'''Generation text''' is a term referring to those members of society who have grown up with [[cell phones]] from a young age. Furthermore, it can be applied to [[adolescent]]s and [[teenagers]] who feel that they are unable to function without a cell phone.
==Creation of the term== The term ''generation text'' has been created by several people independently. Dr. [[Michael Osit]] published a book in 2008 called "Generation Text". A second invention of the word occurred in 2009 at a [[Lights (musician)|Lights]] concert in Winnipeg, Canada by [[Ian Scott (Manitoba politician)|Ian Scott]]. While at the concert, Scott observed that many of the teenagers were either talking on their cell phones, [[text messaging]], or videoing concert footage using their phones. Also noticing that they appeared to be all of one specific generation, he coined the term "generation text".
